com.brightcove.commons.misc.comparison
Class SafeCompare

java.lang.Object
  com.brightcove.commons.misc.comparison.SafeCompare

public class SafeCompare
extends java.lang.Object

Provides mechanisms to compare two objects, guarding against the chance that one or both might be null

equals

public static <T> SafeComparisonResult equals(java.util.List<T> a,
                                              java.util.List<T> b)

Compares two Lists of generic type to each other, guarding against the chance that one or both might be null.

Type Parameters:
T - Type of objects in each list
Parameters:
a - First object to compare
b - Second object to compare
Returns:
"both null", "neither null", or result of "do a and b contain all of the same elements such that a.get(key).equals(b.get(key))?" (order does not matter)
